# Midnight Edge — Components & Motion

Component shapes, interaction states, and animations must align with Midnight Edge tokens in [`src/config/theme.ts`](src/config/theme.ts).

## Button Specifications

Primary buttons:

- Fill: `colors.primary.default` (`#7C3AED`)
- Active/pressed: `colors.primary.active` (`#6D28D9`)
- Shape: `borderRadius.full` (pill)

Form inputs:

- Shape: `borderRadius.md` (12px sharp corners)
- Background: `colors.depth.level1`
- Border: `colors.border.level1`

Gamified badges (XP, level, streak):

- Shape: `borderRadius.full` (pill)

```tsx
// BAD — square corners, hardcoded colors, timing animation
<Pressable
  style={{ backgroundColor: "#7C3AED", borderRadius: 4, padding: 12 }}
  onPress={onPress}
>
  <Text style={{ color: "#fff" }}>Book Now</Text>
</Pressable>

// GOOD — Midnight Edge primary pill button
import { useTheme } from "@/hooks/useTheme";
import { toTextStyle } from "@/config/theme";

const PrimaryButton = ({ label, onPress }: PrimaryButtonProps): React.JSX.Element => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();
  const [pressed, setPressed] = useState(false);

  return (
    <Pressable
      onPress={onPress}
      onPressIn={() => setPressed(true)}
      onPressOut={() => setPressed(false)}
      style={{
        backgroundColor: pressed
          ? theme.colors.primary.active
          : theme.colors.primary.default,
        borderRadius: theme.borderRadius.full,
        paddingHorizontal: theme.spacing.stackLg,
        paddingVertical: theme.spacing.stackMd,
      }}
    >
      <Text style={[toTextStyle(theme.typography.labelMd), { color: theme.colors.text.onPrimary }]}>
        {label}
      </Text>
    </Pressable>
  );
};
```

## Spring Physics Animations

All layout and element transitions must use Reanimated `withSpring` configured from `theme.motion.spring`:

- Stiffness: `300`
- Damping: `20`

Do not use `Animated.timing`, `LayoutAnimation`, or `withTiming` for interactive transitions.

```tsx
// BAD — timing-based layout animation
Animated.timing(opacity, { toValue: 1, duration: 300, useNativeDriver: true }).start();

// GOOD — spring physics from theme tokens
import { useSharedValue, withSpring, useAnimatedStyle } from "react-native-reanimated";
import { useTheme } from "@/hooks/useTheme";

const useMidnightSpring = () => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();
  return {
    stiffness: theme.motion.spring.stiffness,
    damping: theme.motion.spring.damping,
  };
};

// In component:
const spring = useMidnightSpring();
progress.value = withSpring(1, { stiffness: spring.stiffness, damping: spring.damping });
```

Align with [mobile-animations skill](.cursor/skills/mobile-animations/SKILL.md) for UI-thread worklet rules.

## Skeleton Loading States

Skeleton screens must shimmer with a diagonal gradient animating across a dark base layer:

- Base color: `theme.motion.skeletonBase` (`#1A1A24` — same as `colors.depth.level2`)
- Animate gradient sweep via Reanimated — not opacity pulsing on a gray block

```tsx
// BAD — flat gray placeholder block
<View style={{ width: "100%", height: 16, backgroundColor: "#333", borderRadius: 4 }} />

// GOOD — skeleton base from theme token
<View
  style={{
    width: "100%",
    height: 16,
    backgroundColor: theme.motion.skeletonBase,
    borderRadius: theme.borderRadius.sm,
    overflow: "hidden",
  }}
>
  {/* Reanimated diagonal shimmer gradient overlay */}
</View>
```

## Iconography — 1.5pt Thin Stroke

All interface icons must use `theme.icon.strokeWidth` (1.5pt) thin-stroke line icons.

Active/selected icons must project a subtle glow matching their active color state:

```tsx
// GOOD — active icon with color-matched glow
<Icon
  size={24}
  strokeWidth={theme.icon.strokeWidth}
  color={isActive ? theme.colors.primary.default : theme.colors.text.secondary}
  style={
    isActive
      ? {
          shadowColor: theme.colors.primary.default,
          shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 0 },
          shadowOpacity: 0.5,
          shadowRadius: 6,
        }
      : undefined
  }
/>
```

## Premium Milestone Gradient

High-tier ranking badges and premium milestones must use the dual-color linear gradient:

- Start: `#7C3AED` — End: `#EC4899`
- Source: `colors.gradient.premium` via `expo-linear-gradient`

```tsx
import { LinearGradient } from "expo-linear-gradient";

<LinearGradient
  colors={[theme.colors.gradient.premium[0], theme.colors.gradient.premium[1]]}
  start={{ x: 0, y: 0 }}
  end={{ x: 1, y: 0 }}
  style={{ borderRadius: theme.borderRadius.full, padding: theme.spacing.stackSm }}
>
  {/* badge content */}
</LinearGradient>
```
